track_notes:
Hoback Peak is an adventurous climb. It is very remote  and strenuous, and the route finding is difficult: the final 200 feet to the summit is VERY steep dirt. And it is a very beautiful wild area; you are unlikely to find other climbers on the summit.

If you use my track, use the down / right track after mile 4. This is a much better route to the summit.

There is a good trail for the first 3.5 miles. After that, there is a use trail that will take you up the VERY steep grade to timberline. Once at timberline, follow my down track.

Also, you can find alternate tracks online that use a break in the cliff band to gain the east-west summit ridge. 

There is OK cell coverage and plenty of room for wire antennas.
